MAVEN JAVA PROJECT — SHORT & CLEAN STEPS
 Step-1: Open Eclipse IDE for Enterprise Java & Web Developers.
 Step-2: Go to File → New → Maven Project.
 Step-3: In Filter, type quickstart → wait for artifacts.
 Step-4: Select maven-archetype-quickstart → 1.4 → Next.
 Step-5: Enter GroupId: SE, ArtifactId: MavenJava → Next.
 Step-6: Console waits with Y → type Y.
 Step-7: Project appears with pom.xml.
 Step-8: Open App.java.
 Run Maven Phases:
 Maven Clean, Install, Test, Build.
 In Goals type: clean install test → Apply → Run.
 Output: Hello World.
 MAVEN WEB PROJECT — SHORT & CLEAN STEPS
 Step-1: Open Eclipse.
 Step-2: New → Maven Project.
 Step-3: Type webapp.
 Step-4: Select maven-archetype-webapp → 1.4.
 Step-5: GroupId: SE, ArtifactId: MavenWeb.
 Step-6: Console → press Y.
 Step-7: Project created.
 Step-8: Open index.jsp.
 Add Servlet Dependency:
 Search Java Servlet API on mvnrepository.com → paste dependency in pom.xml.
 Configure Tomcat:
 Show View → Servers → Add Server → Tomcat v9/v11.
 Set ports → Admin: 0, HTTP: 8085.
 Add tomcat-users:
 Paste roles & user entry in tomcat-users.xml.
 Run Maven Phases:
 Clean, Install, Test, Build.
 Goals → clean install test.
 Run Web Project:
index.jsp → Run on Server.
